Print a Path Summary for a Fit from sgdnet

Source: R/print.sgdnet.R
print.sgdnet.Rd

Print a Path Summary for a Fit from sgdnet

# S3 method for sgdnet
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x

an object of class 'sgdnet', typically the result of calling sgdnet()
...

other arguments passed to print()

Value

Prints (and return invisibly) a table of the regularization path from the fit with the following columns:

Dfpseudo-degrees of freedom, namely the number of non-zero coefficients
%Devthe percentage of deviance explained
Lambdathe \(\lambda\) value (regularization strength) of the fit

See also

sgdnet(), print.sgdnet()

Examples

fit <- sgdnet(with(mtcars, cbind(drat, hp)), mtcars$disp)
print(fit, digits = 1)
